</P>
<P>
   1. Check in your yellow pages and with local craft councils to
find bookbinders and papermakers. The Robert C. Williams American
Museum of Papermaking at Institute of Paper Science and Technology
 &QL; http://www.ipst.edu/amp/
</P>
<P>
   &QR;  offers useful links to papermakers,
museums and associations. Telephone 1-800-558-6611 in Atlanta, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   2. The Center for the Book in the Library of Congress
 &QL; http://lcweb.loc.gov/loc/cfb ook/ &QR;  was established to stimulate
public interest in books, reading and libraries and to celebrate
the printed word. It offers regional listings of book events, book
fairs and other literary activities, including programs that
promote reading. It also has affiliates in many states. Contact by
telephone: (202) 707-6221.
</P>
