   1. The Parapsychology Association  &QL; http://www.parapsych.org/ &QR; ,
member of the American Association of the Advancement of Science,
provides links to universities, organizations, laboratories and
research, including peer-reviewed papers.
</P>
<P>
   2. The Association for Research and Enlightenment
 &QL; http://www.are-cayce.com/links.htm &QR; , founded by Edgar Cayce in
1931, lists study groups and conferences around the country. Phone
1-800-333-4499.
</P>
<P>
   3. The Rhine Research Center  &QL; http://www.rhine.org/ &QR;  grew out
of the Duke University Parapsychology Laboratory. Phone
919-688-8241. Website has links to other parapsychology research
centers and a public information service.
</P>
<P>
   __ Or, for information on real-time travel to our panelists'
favorite places, visit the U.S. State Department Passport Services
and Information website: (http://travel.state.gov/passport). It
lists more than 3,600 local sites to apply for a passport and visa
nationwide.
</P>
<P>
   For questions about passports, contact the National Passport
Information Center: 1-888-362-8668 or 1-900-225-5674.
</P>
