<P>
   AUCTION (Kansas City, Mo.) _ Great Plains Galleries, an antique
auction house in Lone Jack, has signed with livebid.com to do a
live in-person and Internet auction Saturday. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The company is selling fine arts, including some high-dollar art
glass and a $25,000 painting. It's the Lone Jack company's way of
being competitive. By David Hayes, with photo. (Business desk)
Story will move on the ``f'' wire.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   PAY (Kansas City, Mo.) _ Payless Cashways Inc. said its stores
in and around Littleton, Colo., are working with authorities after
reports surfaced that potential suspects in the Columbine High
School tragedy may have bought some materials in these stores. By
Jennifer Mann. (Business desk) Story will move on the ``f'' wire.
</P>
<P>
   &QL;
</P>
<P>
   STAFF-COMMENTARY (Kansas City, Mo.) _ The 9-year-old Americans
with Disabilities Act said employers couldn't discriminate against
qualified disabled workers and must provide reasonable
accommodation to allow them to perform the jobs. &QL;
</P>
<P>
   But what's a disability? What's reasonable accommodation? Those
questions and more might be further clarified by the U.S. Supreme
Court, which this week is hearing three ADA-related cases. At work
column. By Diane Stafford. Story will move on the ``k'' wire.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   RESER (Kansas City, Mo.) _ An interview with several area
residents who'll be shipping out for the Kosovo engagement.
TENTATIVE. By Dawn Bormann. Story will move on the ``a'' wire.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   WARM (Kansas City, Mo.) _ Global warming conference in Kansas
City to focus on the impact of temperature changes on the Midwest.
By Mike Mansur. Story will move on the ``a'' wire.  &QL;
</P>
<P>
   MILL (Kansas City, Mo.) _ Mayor Kay Barnes, in a conference call
with Hillary Clinton, discovers Wednesday that Kansas City has been
named a millennium city. We'll find out exactly what that honor
implies. Lynn Horsley. 10 inches. Story will move on the ``a''
wire.
</P>
