Endowment for the Arts and the National Endowment for the
Humanities appear Wednesday before a House Appropriations
subcommittee to defend President Clinton's request for a 50 percent
funding increase. It will be the first appearance before the panel,
which has a history of hostility toward the agencies, since Bill
Ivey and Bill Ferris were appointed. (Dart, Cox News Service). 25.
