don't plan to pursue Social Security reform, Rep. Bill Archer,
chairman of the House Ways and Means Committee, and Rep. E. Clay
Shaw, chairman of its Social Security subcommittee, unveil a reform
plan Wednesday. (Lipman, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
<P>
   TEEN-SEX - WASHINGTON - Teen pregnancy, birth and abortion rates
are declining, according to new studies, and another study says one
factor is that peer pressure on teens making sexual decisions is
more likely to be positive influence than a negative one.
(Mollison, Cox News Service). 25.
</P>
