</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ The 602nd-bestselling book among the 2 million offered
by Internet bookstore Amazon.com is currently out of stock; anyone
who wants to buy Margaret Edson's ``Wit'' is warned it will take up
to five weeks to get one. That's because Faber and Faber,
publishers of the $12 paperback, printed only a few thousand
copies. Play scripts recycled as books never sell particularly
well, and, until the middle of April, ``Wit'' was no exception. But
the Pulitzer Prize for drama changed that. By JEFF GUINN. Story has
moved in ``e'' entertainment category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
