<P>
   EASY MEALS &QL;
</P>
<P>
   UNDATED _ It never fails. The air conditioning has gone out in
the car, the traffic leaving work in north Dallas is awful, and
Junior awaits chauffeur service. And when you finally make it to
the preschool, what are the Next Generation's words of greeting?
``What's for dinner, Mom?'' If Mom is lucky, Junior's preschool is
on one of the routes serviced by Easy Street. This nascent
home-meal replacement operation, based in Fort Worth, cooks meals
like Mom would make if Mom had the time. But instead of delivering
the meals individually, a la Domino's, the firm delivers weekly to
each of 49 preschools. By BEVERLY BUNDY. Story has moved in ``d''
food and dining category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL;
