distribution deal with a portal, believed to be Yahoo!. We'll try
to talk to some analysts who were at a private briefing with
Yahoo!'s President, which is when he reportedly said he was up for
buying some or all of the Metro Atlanta company. (Clothier, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BANK-SALE _ BB&AMP;T Corp. will buy First Liberty Financial for $500
million in stock, its second acquisition of a Georgia bank this
year. Winston-Salem-based BB&AMP;T will have offices from Maryland to
southern Georgia after completing four bank purchases. (Harte,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   MINDSPRING _ MindSpring will beef up the content of its portal
site in the hopes of turning it into a money maker. In a conference
call, MindSpring Chief Executive Charles Brewer told Wall Street
analysts the company would either make the investment itself or
seek partnerships with media companies. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   BOOK-HOMEDEPOT _ It's bagels with Bernie at Chapter 11 bookstore
in Atlanta. Bernie Marcus signs his tell-all book, ``Built From
Scratch: How a Couple of Regular Guys Grew the Home Depot from
Nothing to $30 Billion.'' It's a real back-slapping, macho look the
company's early days. Roush's book, ``Inside Home Depot'' hit the
shelves at the same time. If you like cussin' and fussin', stick
with Bernie's. WITH PHOTO.
</P>
