<HEADLINE>
MUSIC REVIEW: EMINEM 
 FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE 
 FROM THE FORT WORTH STAR-TELEGRAM
</HEADLINE>
  World rights. 
 Includes one color slide of  
 By ANGELICA LARA 
 Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) 
<TEXT>
<P>
   EMINEM
</P>
<P>
   Did you ever think a CD could make you sick?
</P>
<P>
   Well, I didn't think it was possible, until I listened to the
new Eminem CD, ``The Slim Shady LP,'' which recently spawned the
hit song ``My Name Is.''
</P>
<P>
   After hearing only half of it, I turned it off in disgust. It
was nothing but a big mix of everything your parents told you to
stay away from.
</P>
<P>
   The songs talk about inappropriate topics, then made it seem
like no big deal. It also made fun of real problems. It's nothing
but one big joke _ and not a very funny one.
</P>
<P>
   &QL; 
 &UR; -0- &QL; 
 &UR; Copyright 1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram &QL; 
 &UR; (Distributed by New York Times Special Features) &QL;
