<HEADLINE>
MADELINE ALBRIGHT: `DRIVEN BY HER OWN BIOGRAPHY'  
 WHO SAYS WE CAN'T STOP EVERY GENOCIDE IN THE WORLD? 
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SLATE, the premier online magazine of politics and culture, is
now available to your readers from The New York Times Syndicate.
</P>
<P>
   Today:
</P>
<P>
   1. MADELINE ALBRIGHT: `DRIVEN BY HER OWN BIOGRAPHY' by A.O.
Scott
</P>
<P>
   Madeleine Albright is a ``celebrity.'' Of her predecessors, only
Henry Kissinger exercised a comparable hold over the public
imagination. Albright's celebrity is less a matter of what she has
done than of who she is.
</P>
<P>
   1,900 words. Slugged: BC-ALBRIGHT-ASSESS-SLATE-NYTSF
</P>
