<P>
   2. WHO SAYS WE CAN'T STOP EVERY GENOCIDE? by Lucy Russell
</P>
<P>
   Critics say moral consistency requires us to do nothing in
Kosovo because we can't intervene every time a thug like Yugoslav
President Slobodan Milosevic decides to start slaughtering his own
citizens. That's not the only argument against the Kosovo
intervention. But is it true?
</P>
