<P>
   LA-SCHOOL-REFORM (Los Angeles) _ A day after the Los Angeles
school board adopted a get-tough policy to restructure failing
schools, the Los Angeles Unified School District identified
campuses that could go into receivership. Superintendent Ruben
Zacarias says 30 schools are at highest risk of being taken over by
district officials. By David R. Baker. (Will move in the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   ANTHRAX-VACCINE (Los Angeles) _ Pvt. 1st Class Roman Lezo of
Sherman Oaks, Calif., may be the first U.S. soldier court-martialed
for refusing to take the military's mandated anthrax vaccine. On
Wednesday, Lezo pleaded not guilty at his arraignment in Hawaii. By
Phillip W. Browne. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   GAS-OUT (Sacramento, Calif.) _ As supporters lobby to build
interest in a national gasoline boycott Friday, lawmakers in
Sacramento who have been deluged by complaints from motorists are
holding a hearing to determine the cause of California's climbing
gasoline prices. By Terri Hardy and Rick Orlov. (Will move in the
``a'' national and ``n'' California news files.)
</P>
<P>
