<P>
   KOSOVO-CONGRESS (Washington) _ The House votes to deny funding
for any U.S. ground forces in Kosovo unless President Clinton first
gets permission from Congress to deploy them. Earlier, Clinton
promised he would do that. House members also are expected to
defeat a resolution that would declare war against Yugoslavia and
one that would require Clinton to withdraw troops now in the
Balkans. By JENNIFER CORBETT DOOREN. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   APACHE-KOSOVO (Washington) _ As the much-touted Apache
