accused in the brutal dragging death of a black man. Lawrence
Russell Brewer, 32, is accused in the June 7, 1998, slaying of
James Byrd Jr., 49. By RICHARD STEWART. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   TOBACCO-TEXAS (Austin, Texas) _ Texas Attorney General John
Cornyn asks for a possible courtroom face-off with his predecessor,
Dan Morales, over a claim by a Morales friend for about $260
million in legal fees in the state's case against the tobacco
industry. By CLAY ROBISON. (Already filed.)
</P>
<P>
   EDUCATION-TEXAS (Austin, Texas) _ The Texas Senate is scheduled
to debate a school finance bill that seeks tax relief for property
owners. But the debate could turn nasty if Republicans try to
attach a voucher amendment to the legislation. By KATHY WALT.
</P>
