<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    CheckFree reports electronic account glitch
 &HT;    By Mark Clothier
 &HT;    c.1999 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ As many as 500,000 people who do their banking from
PCs using Quicken and Microsoft Money software could be having
trouble accessing their accounts because of problems with
CheckFree's equipment, a spokeswoman confirmed Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   The electronic payment platform has not crashed, said CheckFree
spokeswoman Laurinda Wilson.
</P>
<P>
   Those affected are the software-based home-banking customers of
the 20 banks _ including First Union _ that have been moved to
CheckFree's new Genesis technology platform. Customers have had
intermittent problems since Monday, Wilson said.
</P>
<P>
   This is the first service interruption of this magnitude at
CheckFree, Wilson said. CheckFree processes electronic payments for
2.8 million people and handles 11 million transactions a month.
</P>
<P>
   CheckFree said earlier this week it has the potential to manage
70 percent of the telecommunications bills in the country.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
