where economic turmoil and sagging currencies sent cheap steel
flooding to American shores, pushing down prices here. Weirton's
workers, along with those of other big, old-line steel companies,
have gone to Washington by the busload to promote a measure that
would impose quotas on imported steel and roll back imports to
pre-1998 levels. (Gary Tramontina/New York Times Photo)
