A7123 &Cx1f; taf-z
u k &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-EDIT-TELECOMS-MERGER-     04-28 0312
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-EDIT-TELECOMS-MERGER-NYT </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
EDITORIAL: A GERMAN-ITALIAN MERGER 
</HEADLINE>
  (af) 
 c.1999 N.Y. Times News Service   
<TEXT>
<P>
   The New York Times said in an editorial for Thursday, April 29: &QL;
</P>
<P>
   The economic integration of Western Europe, as signified by the
common euro currency, was designed in part to help European
businesses unify to become world-class competitors that could
compete with giant American companies. A merger of Deutsche Telekom
and Telecom Italia is unlikely to produce such a company.
</P>
<P>
   The merger, agreed to last week, would create one of the largest
telecommunications companies in the world, as measured by market
value. But for that company to be an effective competitor it would
need to pursue efficiencies under a management dedicated to making
money and improving service. Nationalistic interests would need to
take a back seat.
</P>
<P>
   But those goals seem to have been overlooked in this deal. The
merged company is to be managed on the basis of ``parity,'' with
neither old company dominating the merged entity and the German
government agreeing not to meddle in management although it will
own 45 percent of the stock.
</P>
<P>
   This is a marriage born of desperation, not of love. The Italian
company wants to fend off a hostile takeover offer from Olivetti, a
much smaller Italian concern. Deutsche Telekom and Telecom Italia _
once state-owned monopolies in their countries _ have been
struggling with the deregulated and internationalized
telecommunications market. They have entered into a variety of
foreign alliances that so far have shown little in the way of
results.
</P>
<P>
   It will be difficult for a merged Italian-German business to
overcome internecine rivalries and provide superior service at a
reasonable cost. If it fails to do so, the result will be a huge
company that will gradually see its markets picked off by more
nimble competitors.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
